HEADWORD: Laryngophony
<hw>Lar`yn*goph"o*ny</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Larynx</ets> + Gr. (<?/) voice.]</ety> <def>The sound of the
voice as heard through a stethoscope when the latter is placed upon the
larynx.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

